status: MARC21-007: Kind of color stock or print of motion picture
Type of color film stock or color print the item represents.

definition (en): Film color prints created by the transfer of two or more differently colored dye images to a single strip of blank film. The dye transfer process was used only to produce prints. Imbibition dye transfer prints can be produced from film originally shot on either multi-strip or multi-layer film.
scope note (en): The process was used only by the Technicolor Company from ca. 1928 to ca. 1975. The patents were sold to the People's Republic of China, and since ca. 1980, the process has been available only in China.

definition (en): Color film stock with three layers of emulsion: cyan, magenta and yellow. Each layer is sensitive to its own primary color.
scope note (en): Since the early 1950's, most color films have been both shot and printed on this stock. It is also called multilayer film stock.

definition (en): Color film stock with three layers of emulsion: cyan, magenta and yellow. Each layer is sensitive to its own primary color and stabilized to reduce color fading as much as possible.
scope note (en): It has been available since ca. 1983.

definition (en): Color print stock with emulsion on both sides. Usually one side is dyed red, and the other side is dyed or toned blue.
Item is not a color film.
Item is not a color film.
